article.headline: High Point 79, Greensboro 42
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Danny Gathings scored 12 points to lead High Point to a 79-42 win over Greensboro College Thursday night. Akeem Scott added 11 points and seven steals while Issa Konare collected 10 rebounds for the Panthers (2-4). High Point held the Pride (2-4) to 28 percent shooting from the field and forced 27 turnovers. Truman Newman led the Pride with a game-high 13 points. Eddie Montrell grabbed eight boards for Greensboro. Greensboro jumped out to a quick 10-4 lead behind five points and an assist from Newman. The Panthers took their first lead of the game (16-15) on a layup by Gathings at the 7:44 mark, and Gathings' jumper with 5:48 left before halftime gave him 1,000 points for his three-years at High Point. High Point closed the first half on a 20-9 run and took a 32-24 lead at the break. The Panthers held Greensboro to just six field goals after halftime and scored 18 of the first 24 points of the final stanza to put things away. High Point outscored the Pride 47-18 in the second half.
